Rating: 3
I reduced the cardamom by 1/4 tsp. because it is a strong spice and I was a little wary. The recipe is right on, though, so next time I'll be using all of it. I also followed other reviewers' advice and only added 1/4 cup of the sugar, which turned out to be plenty. This is a lovely applesauce and a very nice change from the usual cinnamon.

Rating: 4
I've been looking for an applesauce receipe similar to my Grandma's (who was of Swedish decent) for many years and this is exactly what hers tasted like. It's the cardamom! Don't let the smell of the spice deter you from making it. I left it chunky and put a dollup of whip cream on top to make a light dessert. Next time I make an apple pie, I'm using caradmom instead of cinnamon! Delicious.

Rating: 3
A very nice applesauce, not too sweet, good flavor. My family doesn't like a lot of cinnamon flavor, and this was a great alternative.

