Rating: 4
This recipe has been a big hit at my husband's office. He makes it every year since this recipe appeared in Bon Appetit several years ago for his office Thanksgiving potluck. Delicious and elegant.

Rating: 4
I have been making this recipe yearly since 1995. I make enough to freeze for the winter. My husband and small children love it. Some modifications: I also cut the brown sugar in half, I add very little water and use either Melrose or Jonnygold apples. I'll be making this for my grandchildren!

Rating: 3
This is a tasty apple sauce. I would use only 1/2 of the brown sugar next time. Instead of cardamom only, I used 1/2 cardomom and 1/2 cinnamon - very tasty. There was no need to use the food processor. The apples (with a little help from my cooking spoon) cooked down just fine.

